-------------------------------------------------------------------------

* who (list who all currently logged in)

* whoami (see current user)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

* su (switch user - by default root)

* sudo bash (switch to root, if su doesn't work)

* su murthi

* sudo (to execute admin cmds being normal user)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

* sudo useradd murthi (create new user)

* sudo passwd murthi (add password to murthi)

* sudo userdel murthi (delete user)

* sudo groupadd name (create new group)

* sudo groupdel name (delete group)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

* $ means normal user - Ex: /home$

* # means super user - Ex: /home#
